app.application module¶

app.application.create_app(config_obj)[source]¶

Flask application factory. Inializes and returns the Flask application.

This is where blueprints are registered.

Parameters:config_obj (See app.config) – The configuration object to use to initialize the flask application.
Returns:The initialized Flask application.
app.application.get_config(config_class_string)[source]¶

Load the Flask config from a class.

Parameters:config_class_string (str) – The name of the config class to use (See app.config)
Returns:Config object – see app.config

app.extensions module¶

Flask extensions and misc extensions iniatialized here

This currently includes flask_mail and flask_sqlalchemy

app.extensions.db = <SQLAlchemy engine=None>¶

The flask_sqlalchemy object, to be imported and used in other parts of the project.

app.extensions.mail = <flask_mail.Mail object>¶

The flask_mail object, to be imported and used in other parts of the project.
